claim.claim-text:
35. A method of using a cable TV (CATV) distribution system, comprising: 
generating by an uncooled laser a narrowcast optical signal; 
receiving by an optical coupler at a hub both a broadcast optical signal and the narrowcast optical signal; 
generating by the optical coupler a composite optical signal by combining the narrowcast optical signal with the broadcast optical signal; 
providing a CATV node, including an optical demultiplexer, a narrowcast receiver, a broadcast receiver, and an electrical coupler; 
splitting by the optical demultiplexer the composite optical signal into the narrowcast optical signal and the broadcast optical signal; 
receiving by the narrowcast receiver the narrowcast optical signal generated by the optical demultiplexer; 
converting by the narrowcast receiver the narrowcast optical signal into a narrowcast electrical signal; 
receiving by the broadcast receiver the broadcast optical signal generated by the optical demultiplexer; 
converting by the broadcast receiver the broadcast optical signal into a broadcast electrical signal; and 
generating a composite electrical signal by combining the narrowcast electrical signal with the broadcast electrical signal, wherein the generating is accomplished by the electrical coupler.
